headline: CoreWeave stock slips after Q2 results
summary: CoreWeave (CRWV) reported a wider second quarter loss than anticipated. Revenue, however, topped Wall Street estimates, $1.21 billion versus the expected $1.08 billion. Shares fell in the immediate aftermath of the report. Market Domination Overtime Host Allie Canal and Robinhood chief investment officer Stephanie Guild discuss the results. headline: S&P 500, Nasdaq close at fresh record highs
summary: The S&P 500 (^GSPC) closed above 6,400 for the first time on Tuesday. The Nasdaq Composite (^IXIC) also notched a fresh record high, while the Dow Jones Industrial Average (^DJI) ended the day nearly 500 points higher. Stocks got a boost from a tame headline inflation print, which has investors increasing bets that the Fed will cut rates at its next meeting. Yahoo Finance Markets and Data Editor Jared Blikre recaps the action at the close, and Robinhood chief investment officer Stephanie Guild explains why she has a 6,200 target for the S&P 500.  To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.
